## Rules

- Import from the project’s `components/ui` (or path defined in `components.json`), e.g. `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'`.
- Prefer composition: use `asChild` when you need the behavior of a native element (e.g. `Button` wrapping `Link`).
- Don’t recreate existing shadcn components with raw HTML or other libraries; add the shadcn component and use it.
- For one-off layouts that don’t match a primitive (e.g. hero, footer), plain divs + Tailwind are fine; for buttons, inputs, modals, etc., use shadcn.
